# Comprehensive Sentiment Analysis Overhaul

This plan outlines the steps to pivot from simple aggregate sentiment counting to storing detailed, comment-level analysis for specific topics, using the Hugging Face Inference API for speed.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Schema Update (Supabase)
We need a new table in Supabase to hold comprehensive data for every single comment and post fetched.
**New Table: `topic_comments`**
- [id](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/models/topic.py#21-23) (UUID, Primary Key)
- [topic_name](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/models/topic.py#40-42) (Text)
- `post_id` (Text)
- `text` (Text)
- `author` (Text)
- `score` (Integer) - Upvotes/Engagement
- `created_at` (Timestamp)
- `sentiment_label` (Text) - e.g., 'Positive', 'Negative', 'Neutral'
- `confidence_score` (Float) - The probability score from the Hugging Face model

### 2. Backend Logic ([app/utils/fetcher.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/utils/fetcher.py) & [app/utils/analyzer.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/utils/analyzer.py))
- **Modify Reddit Fetcher**: 
  - Change `replace_more(limit=0)` back to `replace_more(limit=None)` for deep scraping.
  - Ensure Reddit author names are extracted.
- **Hugging Face API Integration**:
  - We will build a unified function that takes fetched comments, batches them to the Hugging Face Inference API, and tags them with their `sentiment_label` and `confidence_score`.
  - For the 5 predefined topics, we will write a one-off "seeder" script to fetch the 100 posts, pass them through the API, and dump them into Supabase.
- **Dynamic User Searches**: 
  - If a user searches a custom topic, the backend will fetch 100 posts, send them to the Hugging Face API, stream the visual progress bar, process the data, and generate the visualizations on the fly. 

### 3. Visualizer Updates ([app/utils/visualizer.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/utils/visualizer.py) & [app/controllers/main_controller.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/controllers/main_controller.py))
- Modify `ElectionDataVisualizer` to accept a pandas DataFrame directly instead of exclusively reading from a CSV file.
- [main_controller.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/controllers/main_controller.py) will pull data from the Supabase `topic_comments` table for the predefined topics, convert it to a DataFrame, and pass it to the visualizer.

### 4. Frontend UI ([app/templates/trends.html](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/templates/trends.html))
- Add 5 distinct stylized "Cards" at the top of the Trends page for the predefined topics:
  - Donald Trump
  - The Boys
  - Avengers Doomsday
  - Macbook Neo
  - America vs Iran
- Clicking a card will trigger the backend to pull that topic's pre-analyzed comprehensive data from Supabase and instantly render the visualizations.
- The custom search bar will remain, fetching fresh data from Reddit and the HF API when used.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Since `replace_more(limit=None)` and `limit_posts=100` makes a massive amount of network requests, fetching a custom topic dynamically might take 5-10 minutes on the user's end. We will keep the progress bar to show them it is working!
> - You mentioned you do not have a Hugging Face API Key yet. You will need to create a free account at huggingface.co, generate a token in your settings, and place it in your [.env](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/.env) as `HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY` before we can run the analysis. We will use the standard `cardiffnlp/twitter-roberta-base-sentiment` model.

Do you approve of this detailed breakdown and the database schema?
